description:
Redevelopment by the erection of 50 residential units as
shown on drawings nos. 117/1/19  1A  2A  3C  4B  5A  6A
8B  9  10  11B  12C  13  14  15  16 and 17; L(PL)01-14
inclusive and wd/sk5; as revised by letter dated 13th
October 1995.
decision_conditions:
Condition : 1 - The development must be begun not later than either five
    years from the date of this permission or two years from
    the final approval of the reserved matters, whichever is
    the later.

Condition : 2 - All architectural features to the front elevation shall be
    retained and restored where possible to the satisfaction of
    the Council. Full details of reinstatement of missing
    architectural features shall be submitted to and approved
    by the Council before the start of redevelopment.

Condition : 3 - The facing materials to be used on the the building shall
    not be otherwise than as shall have been submitted to and
    approved by the Council before any work on the site is
    commenced.

Condition : 4 - No development shall take place until full details of hard
    and soft landscaping and means of enclosure of all unbuilt,
    open areas have been submitted to and approved by the
    Council.

Condition : 5 - All trees on the site shall be retained, unless shown as
    removed on the approved drawings, and protected from damage
    as shown on drawing no 117/ 1/19 as revised on 13.10.95, to
    the satisfaction of the Council for a period of at least 12
    months from the commencement of development.

Condition : 6 - All hard and soft landscaping works shall be carried out to
    later than the end of the following planting season, with
    others of similar size and species, unless the Council
    gives written consent to any variation.
    a reasonable standard in accordance with the approved
    landscape details by not later than the end of the planting
    season following completion of the development or any phase
    of the development, whichever is the sooner. Any trees or
    areas of planting which, within a period of 5 years from
    the completion of the development, die, are removed, or
    become seriously damaged or diseased, shall be replaced as

Condition : 7 - In order to comply with the provisions of Section 92 of the
    Town and Country Planning Act 1990.

Condition : 8 - To ensure that the existing character of the buildings are
    preserved.

Condition : 9 - To ensure that the Council may be satisfied with the
    external appearance of the building.

Condition : 10 - To ensure that the council may be satisfied with the
    appearance of the development.

Condition : 11 - To ensure that the Council may be satisfied that the
    development will not have an adverse effect on existing
    trees and in order to maintain the character and amenities
    of the area.
